(125, 'Baxi 212 Regular Gas Boiler', 'baxi-212-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Baxi 212 is the least powerful heat only boiler in the 200’s range, with an output of only 12kW. However, this boiler can still heat a small property with up to 10 radiators. If your home has a higher demand for both central heating and hot water, the Baxi 215, 218, 224, and 230 regular boilers are also available.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>With an efficiency rating of 93%, this regular boiler is well known for being a highly reliable regular gas boiler, which can not only help you to lower your carbon footprint but also help to decrease your energy bills.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Regular boilers are ideal for family homes that have a high demand for both central heating and hot water. This is because they are fed with cold water from a water storage tank, which is usually installed in the attic of your home, this is then heated in the boiler and then stored in a hot water cylinder to use when needed.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>However, it is important to note, that if your home has limited space, regular boilers are not recommended. On the plus side, the Baxi 200 range is also available as a combi boiler for smaller homes.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 7, 60, NULL, 'https://www.heatingspareparts.com/content/docs/baxi_41-470-45_baxi_200_heat_installation_and_servicing_manual.pdf?v=17092610132914868905', '1', '12', 'H: 625mm, W: 370mm, D: 270mm', 'N/A', 'A', '3', '93', 12, '71', '<ul><li>An easy-to-read digital screen </li><li>Easy to use controls for maximum control and comfort in your home</li><li>Compatibility to the Megaflo Eco cylinders</li><li>Low-lift weight</li><li>Compact design for easy installation and future servicing</li></ul>', 'finish_1623160186.jpg', 0, '<p>Baxi has a good reliability record and a good customer score according to the Which? annual survey. It’s also well thought of by expert heating engineers, who give Baxi good scores across the board.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Baxi is the fourth-best ranked