(179, 'Glow Worm Ultimate3 25kW System Gas Boiler', 'glow-worm-ultimate3-25kw-system-gas-boiler', '<p>The Glow Worm Ultimate3 25kW system gas boiler is a reliable, compact and lightweight boiler that can be installed neatly inside your standard kitchen cupboard, out of sight, out of mind.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Thanks to its efficiency rating of 89.7% and an ErP A-rating for central heating, this system gas boiler could potentially help you to reduce your carbon footprint as well as your energy bills.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>With an output rating of 25kW, the Ultimate3 system boiler is perfectly suited to medium to larger homes with 1-2 bathrooms and up to 15 radiators.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>It is important to note when purchasing a new or replacement system boiler, that you will need to allow additional space in your home for a hot water storage tank. Mains water is heated and stored in a separate hot water storage tank ready to be used when needed. For this reason, we don’t recommend system boilers for smaller homes with limited space. Glow-worm Ultimate3 is also available as a combi boiler with a 30kW or 35kW output.</p>', 2, 9, 79, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/User_Manuals/Glowworm/ultimate3-25s-operating-manual-0020239563-00-1182713.pdf', '1', '25', 'H: 740mm, W: 418mm, D: 300mm', 'N/A', 'A', '5', '89', 25, '57', '<ul><li>Compact and lightweight design&nbsp;</li><li>An automotive-grade aluminium heat exchanger&nbsp;</li><li>A Grundfos modulating pump to help reduce energy usage and save you money</li><li>A fully backlit LCD digital display screen with easy to use interface</li><li>An inbuilt filling loop to help for straightforward maintenance</li><li>Compatibility with Glow-worm’s MiGo app&nbsp;</li><li>Easy to use controls &nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623323539.jpg', 0, '<p>Glow-worm is an average boiler brand. It has an average reliability record and engineers tend to rate it about average too. Customers who own a Glow-worm tend to like it, and engineers report that it’s easy to get hold of parts and spares.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If you’re considering this boiler brand, it’s worth checking the Which? best boiler brands page to make sure you get a boiler from one of the best boiler manufacturers around.</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Glow Worm Ultimate3 25kW System Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Glow Worm Ultimate3 25kW System Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 11:12:19', '2021-07-14 12:37:44'),
(180, 'Ideal Logic C24 Combi Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-c24-combi-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic C24 combi gas boiler is perfect for smaller homes with a single bathroom and up to 10 radiators with its output of 24.2kW for both hot water and central heating.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic C24 combi boiler has an ErP A-rating and an efficiency of 94%, meaning that this boiler could potentially save you money on your energy bills and also help to lower your carbon footprint. For example, for every £1 spent on heating your home, only 6p is lost to waste gases - this is extremely efficient when you consider older boilers can have low efficiencies of 70%.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If your home requires a higher demand for hot water, both the Ideal Logic C30 and C35 combi boilers are available, with higher outputs of 30.3kW and 35.3kW.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Combi boilers are great for homes that need instant hot water and central heating. As a result of their compact and sleek design, combi boilers are perfect for smaller homes with limited space as they can be neatly installed into your kitchen cupboard.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 80, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Combi-Installation-Manual.pdf', '1', '24', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '9.9', 'A', '2', '94', 24, '69', '<ul><li>Full modulation to low output increases efficiency</li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen</li><li>Built-in frost protection for the winter months</li><li>Easy to use controls for maximum comfort in your home&nbsp;</li><li>10-year warranty on heat exchanger</li><li>A built-in filling loop</li></ul>', 'finish_1623334173.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The total Which? score is based on reliability, owners’ satisfaction with their boiler, the likelihood of them recommending it to a friend, plus the detailed views of heating engineers on how easy Ideal boilers are to repair and service, their build quality, how easy it is to get hold of parts and spares and whether engineers would recommend them to a customer.</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic C24 Combi Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic C24 Combi Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 14:09:33', '2021-07-14 10:00:33'),
(181, 'Ideal Logic C30 Combi Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-c30-combi-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic C30 Combi Gas Boiler is a highly reliable combi gas boiler that has an output of 24.2kW for central heating and an output of 30.3kW for hot water, which is perfect for small to medium-sized homes with 1-2 bathrooms and up to 15 radiators.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic C30 combi boiler also has an ErP A-rating and an efficiency of 94%, which means that this boiler could potentially save you money on your energy bills and also help you to lower your carbon footprint. For example, for every £1 spent on heating your home, only 6p is lost to waste gases - this is extremely efficient when you consider older boilers can have low efficiencies of 70%.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic C30 is a great boiler for smaller homes that need instant hot water and central heating. Combi boilers provide your home with heating and hot water. As a result of their compact and sleek design, combi boilers are perfect for smaller homes with limited space as they don\'t have any additional tanks to connect.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If your home has a higher demand for hot water, the Ideal Logic C35 has an output of 35.3kW. Additionally, the Ideal Logic C24 that has an output rating of 24.2kW, is also available for homes with lesser demand for hot water.</p>', 1, 3, 80, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Combi-Installation-Manual.pdf', '1', '30', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '12.4', 'A', '2', '94', 30, '69', '<ul><li>Full modulation to low output which increases efficiency<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection for the winter months<br></li><li>Easy to use controls for maximum comfort in your home&nbsp;<br></li><li>10-year warranty on heat exchanger<br></li><li>A built-in filling loop</li></ul>', 'finish_1623334469.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br></p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic C30 Combi Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic C30 Combi Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 14:14:29', '2021-07-14 09:37:18'),
(182, 'Ideal Logic C35 Combi Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-c35-combi-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic C35 combi gas boiler is the most powerful in the Ideal Logic range. Thanks to its high-efficiency rating of 94% and an ErP A-rating, the Ideal Logic C35 could potentially help you to lower your energy bills and carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>All three boilers in the Ideal Logic Combi range have an output of 24.2kW for central heating, however, the Ideal Logic C35 has the most powerful hot water output of 35.3kW, which is perfect for a medium-sized home with up to 20 radiators and 1-2 bathrooms.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>However, many smaller homes would not require this demand for hot water and central heating. Therefore, if you are looking for a new or replacement boiler that is less powerful, the Ideal Logic C24 and C30 are also available and may be better suited to your home.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Combi boilers are great for small to medium sized homes that need instant hot water and central heating.</p>', 1, 3, 80, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Combi-Installation-Manual.pdf', '1', '35', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '14.5', 'A', '2', '94', 35, '69', '<ul><li>Full modulation to low output which increases efficiency<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection for the winter months<br></li><li>Easy to use controls for maximum comfort in your home </li><li>10-year warranty on heat exchanger</li><li>A built-in filling loop</li></ul>', 'finish_1623334919.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic C35 Combi Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic C35 Combi Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 14:21:59', '2021-07-14 10:06:22'),
(183, 'Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 24kW Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-combi-esp1-24kw-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 gas boiler is perfect for homes with limited space as it supplies your home with hot water and central heating on demand by using the mains water supply. With a combi boiler, there is no need for any additional hot or cold water tanks as you would need for a system or regular gas boiler.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 gas boiler is compact and lightweight (28.9kg) and is designed to be wall-mounted for easy installation and future maintenance and servicing. Thanks to its size, this gas boiler can fit neatly into your standard kitchen cupboard.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 24kW is great for homes with up to 15 radiators and a bathroom. For homes with a higher demand for heating and hot water, the Ideal&nbsp;Logic ESP1 30kW and 35kW are available.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 81, NULL, 'https://idealheating.com/uploads/documents/Logic-Combi-Esp1-Installation-And-Servicing-222353-1_inst.pdf', '1', '24', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '9.9', 'A', '2', '94', 24, '69', '<ul><li>Compact and lightweight design&nbsp;<br></li><li>Range of flue options<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>A simple diverter value and a two-stage flame sensor<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection for the winter months<br></li><li>Easy to use controls for maximum comfort in your home&nbsp;<br></li><li>A built-in filling loop</li></ul>', 'finish_1623336577.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 24kW Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 24kW Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 14:49:37', '2021-07-14 10:04:44');
