(184, 'Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 30kW Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-combi-esp1-30kw-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic ESP1 30kW is a highly reliable combi boiler that acts as your central heating and hot water provider, removing the need for a bulky tank or cylinder. Thanks to its compact and lightweight size this combi boiler is easy to install and fits nicely into your standard kitchen cupboard.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic ESP1 30kW is perfect for medium-sized homes with between 15-20 radiators and 1-2 bathrooms. With an efficiency rating of 94% and an ErP A-rating for central heating and hot water, this combi boiler could potentially help you to reduce both your energy bills and carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic ESP1 is also available in 24kW for homes with a lesser demand for heating and hot water, however, if your home requires a more powerful boiler, then the Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 35kW is also available, which may be perfect for your home.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 81, NULL, 'https://idealheating.com/uploads/documents/Logic-Combi-Esp1-Installation-And-Servicing-222353-1_inst.pdf', '1', '30', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '12.4', 'A', '2', '94', 30, '69', '<ul><li>Compact and lightweight design&nbsp;<br></li><li>Range of flue options<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>A simple diverter value and a two-stage flame sensor</li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen</li><li>Built-in frost protection for the winter months<br></li><li>Easy to use controls for maximum comfort in your home&nbsp;<br></li><li>A built-in filling loop</li></ul>', 'finish_1623336903.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 30kW Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 30kW Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 14:55:03', '2021-07-14 13:19:50'),
(185, 'Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 35kW Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-combi-esp1-35kw-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 35kW is an all-rounder, acting as a water heater and central heating boiler. With an efficiency rating of 94% and an ErP A rating, the Ideal Logic is known for its reliability and its ability to reduce your energy bills.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>This combi boiler is ideal for homes that have a high demand for both central heating and hot water. The Logic Combi ESP1 35kW has the power to heat a larger-sized home with up to 20 radiators and 2 bathrooms. However, if your home does not require such a powerful output, there is also the 24kW and the 30kW available for small to medium-sized homes.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 is designed to be compact and lightweight, helping with easy installation and access and more cost-effective maintenance and servicing in the future. Thanks to its compact design, this combi boiler can be installed neatly in replacement of your standard kitchen cupboard.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 81, NULL, 'https://idealheating.com/uploads/documents/Logic-Combi-Esp1-Installation-And-Servicing-222353-1_inst.pdf', '1', '35', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '14.5', 'A', '2', '94', 35, '69', '<ul><li>Compact and lightweight design&nbsp;<br></li><li>Range of flue options<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>A simple diverter value and a two-stage flame sensor<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection for the winter months<br></li><li>Easy to use controls for maximum comfort in your home&nbsp;<br></li><li>A built-in filling loop</li></ul>', 'finish_1623337092.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 35kW Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic Combi ESP1 35kW Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 14:58:12', '2021-07-14 10:02:14'),
(186, 'Ideal Logic Max C24 Combi Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-max-c24-combi-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Max Combi boilers are well known for being efficient and reliable gas boilers. With a 94% efficiency rating and ErP A-rating for central heating and domestic hot water, the Ideal Logic Max C24 could potentially help you to lower your energy bills, as well as help lower your carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Max Combi boiler is great for those with limited space in their home. Having a combi boiler installed in your home means there is no need for a hot or cold water tank like you would need for a system or regular gas boiler.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Ideal has designed this boiler model to be compact and sleek, allowing it to fit neatly inside your standard kitchen cupboard.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Max Combi C24 is best suited to homes with up to 15 radiators and a single bathroom, thanks to its central heating and hot water output rating of 24kW. If you require a new or replacement boiler with a higher central heating output, the Ideal Logic Max C30 and C35 combi boilers are available.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 82, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Max-Combi-Inst.pdf', '1', '24', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '9.9', 'A', '10', '94', 24, '69', '<ul><li>Large digital display</li><li>Easily reachable pressure gauge</li><li>An easy to read digital display screen</li><li>Easy to use controls<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind and maximum comfort in your home<br></li><li>A hardwearing and scratch-resistant case for extra longevity<br></li><li>Low lift weight for easy installation&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623337643.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic Max C24 Combi Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic Max C24 Combi Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 15:07:23', '2021-07-14 10:01:05'),
(187, 'Ideal Logic Max C30 Combi Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-max-c30-combi-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Max Combi Gas boiler range can help reduce your heating bills and also your carbon footprint thanks to its brilliant efficiency rating of 94% and an ErP A rating for both central heating and hot water. The Ideal Logic Max C30 combi boiler is known for its reliability and efficiency.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>All of the Ideal Logic Max Combi gas boilers have the same central heating output of 24.2kW, however, they differ in hot water outputs. The Ideal Logic Max C30 Combi gas boiler has a domestic hot water output rating of 30.3kW, great for homes with a bath. If you have a medium to large-sized home, with up to 20 radiators and 1 a single main bathroom, this combi boiler could be the one for you.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>For homes with a lesser demand for central heating and hot water, the Ideal Logic Max C24 (24kW) should be considered. Meanwhile, for larger homes with higher demand, the Ideal Logic Max C35 (35kW) combi boiler is also available.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Combi boilers are ideal for homes with limited space, as they remove the need for any additional cold or hot water tanks like you would need if you had a system or regular boiler installed. This is because combi boilers combine both the water heater and the central heating system in one unit. This also means that they can provide your home with hot water instantly.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 82, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Max-Combi-Inst.pdf', '1', '30', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '12.4', 'A', '10', '94', 30, '69', '<ul><li>Large digital display<br></li><li>Easily reachable pressure gauge<br></li><li>An easy to read digital display screen<br></li><li>Easy to use controls<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind and maximum comfort in your home<br></li><li>A hardwearing and scratch-resistant case for extra longevity<br></li><li>Low lift weight for easy installation&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623338225.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic Max C30 Combi Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic Max C30 Combi Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 15:17:05', '2021-07-15 08:06:18'),
(188, 'Ideal Logic Max C35 Combi Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-max-c35-combi-gas-boiler', '<p>With an efficiency rating of 94% and an ErP A rating, the Ideal Logic Max combi gas boiler range could potentially help reduce your heating bills and also your carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>All three combi boilers in the Ideal Logic Max range have the same central heating output of 24.2kW, however, the hot water output rating varies on the model you choose. The Ideal Logic Max C35 combi gas boiler has the most powerful domestic hot water output rating in the Logic Max range, of 35.3kW, great for larger homes with up to 20 radiators and a single bathroom with a bath. Meanwhile, if your home doesn’t require such a high demand for hot water then the Ideal Logic Max C24 or C30 may be better suited to your home.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Combi boilers are ideal for homes with limited space, this is because they combine both the water heater and the central heating system in one unit, removing the need for any additional hot or cold water tanks that you would typically need for either a system to regular boiler. Thanks to its compact and lightweight design, this combi boiler can be installed neatly in replacement of your standard kitchen cupboard.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 82, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Max-Combi-Inst.pdf', '1', '35', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '14.5', 'A', '10', '94', 35, '69', '<ul><li>Large digital display<br></li><li>Easily reachable pressure gauge<br></li><li>An easy to read digital display screen<br></li><li>Easy to use controls<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;<br></li><li>A hardwearing and scratch-resistant case for extra longevity<br></li><li>Low lift weight for easy installation&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623338565.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic Max C35 Combi Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic Max C35 Combi Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-10 15:22:45', '2021-07-15 08:07:05'),
(189, 'Ideal Logic Plus C24 Combi Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-plus-c24-combi-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Plus C24 is a condensing combi gas boiler, meaning there is no need for a water tank or cylinder as you would need for a system or regular boiler. With a high-efficiency rating of 94% and an ErP A rating, the Ideal Logic Plus C24 is highly reliable and cost-effective.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Plus range all have the same central heating output level of 24.2kW, however, the domestic hot water output level is different with each model. The Ideal Logic Plus C24 has the lowest power of all three boilers in the range but still can heat a smaller home with up to 15 radiators and a bathroom. If you are looking for a new or replacement boiler that can meet higher demand for hot water output, then the Ideal Logic Plus C30 or C35 may be a better option for you.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Combi boilers are ideal for homes with limited space thanks to its compact and lightweight design. The Ideal Logic Plus C24 is perfect for neat installation into your standard kitchen cupboard.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 83, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/logic-1.pdf', '1', '24', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', '9.9', 'A', '7', '94', 24, '69', '<ul><li>Large digital display<br></li><li>Easily reachable pressure gauge<br></li><li>An easy to read digital display screen<br></li><li>Honeywell gas valve&nbsp;<br></li><li>Easy to use controls<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind and maximum comfort in your home<br></li><li>A hardwearing and scratch-resistant case for extra longevity<br></li><li>Low lift weight for easy installation&nbsp;<br></li><li>Built-in filling loop</li></ul>', 'finish_1623399171.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Whi