(197, 'Ideal Vogue Max C40 Combi Gas Boiler', 'ideal-vogue-max-c40-combi-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Vogue Max C40 is the most powerful combi boiler in the range with an efficiency rating of 93% and an ErP A-rating for both central heating and hot water. Thanks to these ratings, this boiler could potentially help you lower both your carbon footprint and your energy bills.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Installing a new or replacement combi boiler in your home means that there will be no need for any additional hot or cold water tanks, which is beneficial for those with limited space in their homes. Combi boilers are ‘ideal’ (excuse the pun) for homes that need instant hot water, this is because the cold water is heated and then delivered to your taps, baths and showers on demand, when needed.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Vogue Max combi boiler is also compact and can be easily wall-mounted. However, this combi boiler is slightly larger than your typical combi boiler so will not fit in the space of a standard kitchen cupboard.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Vogue Max C40 has the highest central heating output rating in the range, with an output of&nbsp;32kW for central heating and 40kW for hot water. With these outputs, this combi boiler is suitable for medium to larger-sized homes with up to 2 bathrooms and 20 radiators. However, many smaller homes will not require this kW output for central heating and hot water. For homes with a lesser demand, the Ideal Vogue Max C26 or C30 would be a more suitable boiler.&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 85, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Vogue-Max-Combi-Installation-Servicing-222378-1_lowres-REDEUCED.pdf', '1', '40', 'H: 740mm, W: 445mm, D: 330mm', '16.4', 'A', '10', '93', 40, '69', '<ul><li>Modern and compact design&nbsp;<br></li><li>An easy to read pressure gauge<br></li><li>Large control panel&nbsp;<br></li><li>A stainless steel heat exchanger<br></li><li>A large LCD display screen<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Low-li