(198, 'Ideal EvoMax 60kW Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-evomax-60kw-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal EvoMax 60kW regular gas boiler is a highly reliable condensing boiler with an efficiency rating of 96.9% and an ErP A-rating for central heating and hot water. &nbsp;With an output rating of 60kW, the EvoMax range is perfect for homes or larger properties with multiple bathrooms and 20+ radiators.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Regular gas boilers are installed with an additional hot water cylinder (typically located in an airing cupboard in your home), your boiler itself will also need to be fed by a cold water storage cistern, which is typically installed in the attic of your home. It is important to make a note of this when considering purchasing a new or replacement regular boiler, as regular boilers are not suitable for smaller homes with limited space.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The EvoMax 60kW is not suitable for properties with limited space due to its size, however, this regular boiler is compact and has a great deal of flexibility when it comes to installation, with the option of either being wall-mounted or floor standing. How? Well, this is because the optional frame and header-kit offers in-line and back to back cascade options. The Ideal EvoMax has been designed with carefully selected components to ensure reliability and efficiency.</p>', 3, 3, 86, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Evomax-Installation-Manual.pdf', '1', '60', 'H: 800mm, W: 500mm, D: 360mm', 'N/A', 'A', '2', '96', 60, '69', '<ul><li>A fully backlit display for easy reading<br></li><li>Simple controls for easy use<br></li><li>5 years warranty of parts and labour for extra peace of mind<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;<br></li><li>Compact and lightweight design&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623402422.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal h