(199, 'Ideal EvoMax 150kW Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-evomax-150kw-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal EvoMax 150kW regular gas boiler has an excellent efficiency rating of 96.7% rating, which is why they are named highly reliable boilers. With an output rating of 150kW, the EvoMax range is perfect for very large homes or properties with multiple radiators and bathrooms. If you are looking for a regular gas boiler with not such a high output rating but still packs a punch, the EvoMax is also available in 60kW.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Regular gas boilers are installed with an additional hot water cylinder (typically located in an airing cupboard in your home). The boiler itself will also need to be fed by a cold water storage cistern, which is typically installed in the attic of the property. It is important to make a note of this when considering purchasing a new or replacement regular boiler, as regular boilers are not suitable for smaller homes with limited space.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Although the EvoMax 150kW is not suitable for properties with limited space, the boiler component itself is compact and has a great deal of flexibility when it comes to where to install it. The EvoMax can either be wall-mounted or floor-standing thanks to the optional frame and header kit which offers in-line or back-to-back cascade.</p>', 3, 3, 86, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Evomax-Installation-Manual.pdf', '1', '150', 'H: 800mm, W: 500mm, D: 360mm', 'N/A', 'A', '2', '96', 150, '69', '<ul><li>A fully backlit display for easy reading<br></li><li>Simple controls for easy use<br></li><li>5 years warranty of parts and labour for extra peace of mind<br></li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;<br></li><li>Compact and lightweight design&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623403498.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliab