(200, 'Ideal Logic Heat H12 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-heat-h12-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Logic Heat H12 is a condensing wall-mountable regular gas boiler, designed and manufactured in the UK.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The low-lift weight of 22.7kg and its compact size makes installation quick and easy, allowing the boiler unit to be fitted easily into your standard kitchen cupboard, out of sight, out of mind. With a highly efficient rating of 93% and ErP A-rating, the Ideal Logic Heat H12 regular boiler could also potentially help to lower your bills and carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Heat H12 is the least powerful in its range, however, it is perfect for smaller homes with up to 10 radiators. If your home requires a higher demand for central heating, Ideal has also designed the H15 (15kW output), the H18 (18kW output), the H24 (24kW output) and even the H30 (30kW output).&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Regular boilers are ‘ideal’ (excuse the pun) for homes with a high demand for instant hot water. This is because they are supplied with cold water, which is then heated in the boiler unit and then stored in a hot water cylinder tank. If your home has limited space, a regular boiler is not recommended due to the fact that an additional hot water storage tank will need to be installed, as well as a cold water cistern and a feed (these are typically installed in the attic of your home). The Ideal Logic range is also available as a combi and system boiler, so there is an option for everyone.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 87, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Heat-Installation-Manual.compressed.pdf', '1', '12', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '2', '93', 12, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchanger</li></ul>', 'finish_1623403809.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic Heat H12 Regular Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic Heat H12 Regular Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-11 09:30:09', '2021-07-14 14:48:40'),
(201, 'Ideal Logic Heat H15 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-heat-h15-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Logic Heat H15 is a condensing, wall-mountable regular gas boiler, designed and manufactured in the UK.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>This boiler is compact and has a low-lift weight of 22.7kg making installation quick and easy. This regular boiler unit can be fitted neatly into your standard kitchen cupboard, out of sight, out of mind.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Regular boilers are ‘ideal’ (excuse the pun) for homes with a high demand for instant hot water. This is because they are supplied with cold water, which is then heated in the boiler unit and then stored in a hot water cylinder tank. </p><p><br></p><p>If your home has limited space, a regular boiler is not recommended due to the fact that an additional hot water storage tank will need to be installed, as well as a cold water cistern and a feed (these are typically installed in the attic of your home). On the plus side, the Ideal Logic range is also available as a combi and system boiler, so there is an option for everyone.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>With a highly efficient rating of 93% and ErP A-rating, the Ideal Logic Heat H15 could potentially help to lower your bills and carbon footprint. The Ideal Logic Heat H15 is not the most powerful option in its range, however, it is perfect for smaller homes with up to 10 radiators and a single bathroom. If your home requires a higher demand for central heating, Ideal has also designed the H18 (18kW output), the H24 (24kW output), and even the H30 (30kW output). Meanwhile, if you feel that 15kW may be too high of a demand for your home, the H12 (12kW output) is also an option.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 87, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Heat-Installation-Manual.compressed.pdf', '1', '15', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '2', '93', 15, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A 