(202, 'Ideal Logic Heat H18 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-heat-h18-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Heat H18 is manufactured in the UK and is known for being a reliable condensing regular gas boiler.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Its compact size and low-lift weight mean that it can be wall-mounted, fitting neatly into your standard kitchen cupboard. So don’t worry, it won’t ruin the aesthetic of the kitchen! However, it is important to note when purchasing a new or replacement boiler that you will need to accommodate for an additional hot water storage tank, which is usually installed in an airing cupboard, as well as a cold water cistern and a feed, typically installed in the attic of a home. For this reason, if your home has limited space, a combi or system boiler is recommended instead. &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Thanks to its efficiency rating of 94% and ErP A-rating for heat, the Ideal Logic Heat is known for its reliability and its ability to help lower your energy bills and carbon footprint.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Heat H18 sits in the middle of the range with regards to output power, with an output of 18kW, perfect for a home with up to 15 radiators. However, if you feel that your home has a higher demand for central heating, Ideal has also designed the H24 (24kW output) and the H30 (30kW output). If you feel that your home does not require this amount of kW output, the H15 (15kW output) and the H18 (18kW output) are also available.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 87, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Heat-Installation-Manual.compressed.pdf', '1', '18', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '2', '93', 18, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading</li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchan