(203, 'Ideal Logic Heat H24 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-heat-h24-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Heat H24 is a reliable regular gas boiler, designed and manufactured in the UK. Thanks to its compact size and low-lift weight, this regular boiler can be wall-mounted and fitted neatly into the space of a standard kitchen cupboard. Out of sight, out of mind.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Regular boilers are ‘ideal’ (excuse the pun) for homes with a high demand for instant hot water. This is because they are supplied with cold water, which is then heated in the boiler unit and then stored in a hot water cylinder tank. </p><p><br></p><p>If your home has limited space, a regular boiler is not recommended due to the fact that an additional hot water storage tank will need to be installed, as well as a cold water cistern and a feed (these are typically installed in the attic of your home). The Ideal Logic range is also available as a combi and system boiler, so there is an option for everyone.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Thanks to its efficiency rating of 93% and ErP A-rating for heat, the Ideal Logic Heat H24 is known for its reliability and its ability to help lower your energy bills and carbon footprint.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Heat H24 is the second most powerful in its range with regards to output power, with an output of 24kW. This is perfect for a home with up to 15 radiators. However, if you feel that your home has a higher demand for central heating, Ideal has also designed the H30 (30kW output). Meanwhile, if you feel that your home does not require this amount of kW output, the H15 (15kW output), the H18 (18kW output), and the H24 (24kW) are also available.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 87, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Heat-Installation-Manual.compressed.pdf', '1', '24', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '2', '93', 24, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></l