(205, 'Ideal Logic Max Heat H12 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-max-heat-h12-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Max Heat H12 has been designed with efficiency in mind. With a rating of 93% and an ErP A-rating for central heating and hot water, this regular boiler could potentially help you to lower your energy bills.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Although the Logic Max H12 is the least powerful regular boiler in this range, it is ‘ideal’ (excuse the pun) for properties with up to 10 radiators and a single bathroom. If your home requires a more powerful boiler with a higher output, the Logic Max range also includes models with outputs of 15kW, 18kW, 24kW and 30kW.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Max Heat is designed to heat your central heating system directly and produce hot water for a cylinder. The hot water cylinder is fed by cold water from a storage cistern, typically located in an attic. Bearing this in mind, regular boilers are often not recommended for homes with limited space. But don\'t panic, the Ideal Logic Max range is available as a combi and system boiler if needed.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 88, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/logic-max-heat-inst.pdf', '1', '12', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '93', 12, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchanger<br></li><li>Hardwearing and scratch-resistant cover<br></li><li>Compatible with Ideal Controls</li></ul>', 'finish_1623408096.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heat