(206, 'Ideal Logic Max Heat H15 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-max-heat-h15-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Max Heat H15 has been designed with efficiency in mind. With a rating of 94% and an ErP A-rating for central heating and hot water, this regular gas boiler could help you to lower your energy bills as well as reduce your carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Max H15 is middle of the range when it comes to power, however, it is perfect for smaller homes with up to 10 radiators and a single bathroom. If your home requires a more powerful boiler then the Logic Max regular boiler range also includes models with outputs of 18kW, 24kW, and 30kW.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Max Heat is a regular boiler that has been designed to provide you with heat and produce hot water for storage in a cylinder. Cold water from a storage cistern&nbsp;is fed to the boiler, typically located in an attic, which is then heated and stored in a hot water tank. This means that regular gas boilers are not suitable for homes with limited space. </p><p><br></p><p>However, the boiler unit itself is compact and can be installed easily in a standard kitchen cupboard. If your home does not have the extra space that\'s needed for a regular boiler, then there is an option to go for the Ideal Logic Max combi boiler.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 88, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/logic-max-heat-inst.pdf', '1', '15', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '94', 15, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchanger<br></li><li>Hardwearing and scratch-resistant cover<br></li><li>Compatible with Ideal Controls</li></ul>', 'finish_1623408416.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal 