(207, 'Ideal Logic Max Heat H18 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-max-heat-h18-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Max Heat H18 is a compact condensing regular gas boiler, which can be installed neatly into your standard kitchen cupboard. However, in addition to the boiler itself, you will also need a hot water cylinder, cold water tank, and expansion tank installed. For this reason, they are not recommended for homes with limited space.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Max Heat H18 regular boiler is perfect for homes that require instant hot water. This is because the boiler is fed by cold water from a tank that is typically located in an attic, heated, and then stored in the cylinder until it\'s needed.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Logic Max Heat H18 has an efficiency rating of 93% and an ErP A-rating, which could potentially help you to reduce your energy bills. With an output level of 18kW, the H18 is middle of the range amongst the 5 Logic Heat regular boilers available and ideal for homes with up to 15 radiators and a bathroom. </p><p><br></p><p>If you are looking for a new or replacement regular boiler that has a higher output level, the Ideal Logic Max Heat 24kW and 30kW are available, also, if your home does not require this demand of output rating, the 12kW and 15kW are also available.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 88, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/logic-max-heat-inst.pdf', '1', '18', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '93', 18, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchanger<br></li><li>Hardwearing and scratch-resistant cover<br></li><li>Compatible with Ideal Controls</li></ul>', 'finish_1623408888.jpg', 0, '<p>Ideal boilers have ma