(208, 'Ideal Logic Max Heat H24 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-max-heat-h24-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>With an efficiency rating of 94% and an ErP A-rating for central heating and hot water, the Ideal Logic Max Heat H24 is a highly reliable regular gas boiler. If you are looking for a new or replacement boiler that can help you to reduce your energy bills, this may be the perfect choice.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Thanks to its compact and lightweight design, this regular boiler can be installed neatly and easily into a standard kitchen cupboard. However, it is important to note that when purchasing a new regular gas boiler, you will need to accommodate space for a cold water cistern (which is usually installed into your attic). This feeds your boiler with cold water that is heated and stored in a hot water cylinder, which you will also need. </p><p><br></p><p>For this reason, this model may not be suitable for those with smaller homes and limited space.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Max Heat H24 is the second most powerful in its range, with an output rating of 24kW, perfect for homes with up to 15 radiators and 1-2 bathrooms. If your home does not require this amount of energy, the Logic Heat range also offers 12kW, 15kW, and 18kW regular boilers. Meanwhile, if you feel that this model does not meet your demands, the Ideal Logic Max Heat H30 is also available which has an output of 30kW.</p>', 3, 3, 88, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-Heat-Installation-Manual.compressed.pdf', '1', '24', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '94', 24, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchanger<br></li><li>Hardwearing and scratch-resistant cover