(209, 'Ideal Logic Max Heat H30 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-max-heat-h30-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Max Heat H30 regular gas boiler has an efficiency rating of 93% and has been awarded an ErP A-rating, making it a highly reliable heat-only boiler but can also help reduce your energy bills and carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>With an output rating of 30kW, the H30 is the most powerful in the Logic Max Heat regular boiler range, perfectly suited to larger properties with up to 20 radiators and 1-2 bathrooms. However, many smaller homes will not require this demand for central heating and hot water. In this case, the Ideal Logic Max Heat range also includes the H12 (12kW output), the H15 (15kW output), the H18 (18kW output), and the H24 which has an output of 24kW. These may be better suited to small to medium-sized properties.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>A replacement regular boiler is best suited to homes that have the existing pipework needed to connect all parts of the central heating system.</p><p><br></p><p> If you are considering purchasing a new regular boiler, it is important to note that although they are great for homes that require instant hot water, you will need space in your home for an additional hot water cylinder and a cold water tank. For this reason, we do not recommend regular boilers for properties with limited space.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 88, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/logic-max-heat-inst.pdf', '1', '30', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '94', 30, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchanger<br></li><li>Hardwearing and scratch-resistant cover<br></li><li>Compatible with Ideal Controls</li></ul>