(210, 'Ideal Logic Plus Heat H12 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-plus-heat-h12-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Plus Heat H12 regular gas boiler has an efficiency rating of 93% and an ErP A-rating for heat. Depending on your current boiler’s efficiency, the Logic Plus Heat H12 could potentially save you money on your energy bills and reduce your carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Logic Plus Heat H12 regular boiler is compact and lightweight so that it can be installed neatly in replacement of a standard kitchen cupboard. However, it is important to note that when purchasing a new or replacement regular gas boiler, you will need to accommodate for the additional cold water tank and feed that is typically located in the attic, as well as a hot water cylinder. </p><p><br></p><p>This is because regular boilers are fed by a cold water cistern, this water is then heated in the unit and stored in a separate hot water cylinder for when needed. For this reason, we don\'t recommend regular boilers to comes with limited space.&nbsp; On the plus side, this means you will have access to instant hot water whenever you need it.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>While the Ideal Logic Plus Heat H12 has the lowest output of the range, it is perfect for smaller properties with up to 10 radiators. For homes with a higher demand for central heating and hot water, the range also includes output ratings of 15kW, 18kW, 24kW and30 kW.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 89, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/logic-plus-heat-inst.pdf', '1', '12', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '7', '93', 12, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchanger<br></li><li>Hardwearing and scratch-resista