(211, 'Ideal Logic Plus Heat H15 Regular Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-plus-heat-h15-regular-gas-boiler', '<p>The Ideal Logic Plus Heat H15 has an efficiency rating of 93% and an ErP A-rating for heat, which could potentially save you money on your energy bills and reduce your carbon footprint.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Plus Heat H15 is a compact condensing heat-only gas boiler, which can be installed neatly into your standard kitchen cupboard with easy installation. Despite the boiler\'s size, it is important to note that when purchasing a new or replacement regular gas boiler, you will need to accommodate for the cold water tank and feed that is typically located in the attic as well as a hot water cylinder. </p><p><br></p><p>Regular boilers are fed by a cold water cistern, this water is then heated in the boiler and stored in a separate hot water cylinder for when needed. For this reason, we don\'t recommend regular boilers to homes with limited space. Regular boilers give you access to instant hot water whenever you need it.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Ideal Logic Plus Heat H15 is one of the range’s least powerful boilers, with an output of only 15kW. However, this output is ideal for homes with up to 10 radiators and a single bathroom. If your home requires a higher demand for central heating and hot water, the Ideal Logic Plus range also has the 18kW, 24kW and 30kW regular boilers available.&nbsp;</p>', 3, 3, 89, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/logic-plus-heat-inst.pdf', '1', '15', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '7', '93', 15, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra peace of mind during the colder months<br></li><li>A fully backlit LCD display screen for easy use and reading<br></li><li>User-friendly controls<br></li><li>Easy to see pressure gauge&nbsp;<br></li><li>Flexible flue installation<br></li><li>10 years warranty on the heat exchanger<br></li><li>Hardwearing and scratch-resistant cover</li><