(232, 'Ideal Logic S30 System Gas Boiler', 'ideal-logic-s30-system-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\">The Ideal Logic S30 system gas boiler is the most powerful boiler in the Logic range, with an output of 30.3kW for central heating. This output is ‘Ideal’ (excuse the pun) for larger homes with up to 20 radiators and up to 2 bathrooms.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">With a high-efficiency rating of 93% and an ErP A-rating for heat, the Ideal Logic System S30 is one of the most efficient system boilers on the market. Depending on your current boilers efficiency rating, this system boiler could potentially help you to save money on your energy bills.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">If your home has lesser demand for central heating and hot water, there are alternative, less powerful system boilers in the Ideal Logic range. These include the S15 (15kW output) the S18 (18kW output) and the S24 with an output of 24kW. These outputs are better suited to homes with between 10 and 15 radiators.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The benefit of having a system boiler is that the water is heated up and then stored in a hot water cylinder where it remains until you need it, whether it be for filling the sink, having a shower, or running a nice bath after a cold winter evening. </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">This type of system can meet higher demands for hot water which is why it is often chosen instead of a combi.&nbsp;</span>However, it is important to note than when purchasing a new or replacement system boiler, that you will need to accommodate room in your home for the hot water cylinder as well as your boiler. Therefore, if your home has limited space, you may want to consider a combi boiler instead.</p>', 2, 3, 94, NULL, 'https://www.freeboilermanuals.com/assets/pdf/ideal/Logic-System-Installation-Manual.pdf', '1', '30', 'H: 700mm, W: 395mm, D: 278mm', 'N/A', 'A', '2', '93', 30, '69', '<ul><li>Built-in frost protection for extra reassurance during those winter months</li><li>A large digital LCD display screen for easy use</li><li>User-friendly heating controls</li><li>A low lift weight for easy installation</li><li>Scratch-resistant casing</li><li>Compact design&nbsp;</li><li>10 years warranty on heat exchanger</li></ul>', 'finish_1623683691.jpg', 0, '<p><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s\r\nwell worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer\r\nscore, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</span><br></p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Logic S30 System Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Logic S30 System Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-14 15:14:51', '2021-07-14 13:35:01'),
(233, 'Ideal Vogue GEN2 S15 System Gas Boiler', 'ideal-vogue-gen2-s15-system-gas-boiler', '<p>With an output rating of 15kW the Ideal Vogue Gen2 S15 system gas boiler is best suited for smaller homes with around 10 radiators and a bathroom. However, if your home requires a higher demand for central heating and hot water, the Ideal Vogue Gen2 range is available in an 18kW, 26kW and even a 32kW system gas boiler.<br></p><p><br></p><p>The Ideal Vogue Gen2 S15 system boiler has an efficiency rating of 92%, which means that depending on your current boilers efficiency rating, this system boiler could potentially help you save money on your energy bills and reduce your carbon footprint levels.</p><p><br></p><p>A system boiler provides you with hot water quite literally \'on tap\' (excuse the pun) as it stores heated water in a storage cylinder, ready for use.</p>', 2, 3, 95, NULL, 'https://idealheating.com/uploads/documents/216174-5-vogue-system-gen2-user-guide.pdf', '1', '15', 'H: 740mm, W: 445mm, D: 330mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '92', 15, '69', '<ul><li>Fitted with premium components</li><li>Multi-function buttons</li><li>Fully backlit 3.5 inches digital LCD display screen</li><li>Easy to read pressure gauge</li><li>Uniform control opening</li><li>Cool door technology</li><li>Stylish aesthetics</li><li>Stainless steel heat exchanger</li><li>Low lift weight&nbsp;</li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623684093.jpg', 0, '<p><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s\r\nwell worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer\r\nscore, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</span><br></p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Vogue GEN2 S15 System Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Vogue GEN2 S15 System Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-14 15:21:33', '2021-07-14 09:56:40'),
(234, 'Ideal Vogue GEN2 S18 System Gas Boiler', 'ideal-vogue-gen2-s18-system-gas-boiler', '<p>With an output rating of 18kW the Ideal Vogue Gen2 S18 system gas boiler is best suited for smaller homes with around 15 radiators and a bathroom. However, if your home requires a higher demand for central heating and hot water, the Ideal Vogue Gen2 range is available in as a 26kW and even 32kW system gas boiler. Meanwhile, for homes with a lesser demand, the 15kW model is also available.</p><p><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Ideal Vogue Gen2 S18 system boiler has an efficiency rating of 93%, which means that depending on your current boilers efficiency rating, this system boiler could potentially help you save money on your energy bills and reduce your carbon footprint.</p><p><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A system boiler can provide you with hot water quite literally \'on tap\' (excuse the pun). This is because system boilers store heated water in a storage tank, ready for when it\'s needed.</p>', 2, 3, 95, NULL, 'https://idealheating.com/uploads/documents/216174-5-vogue-system-gen2-user-guide.pdf', '1', '18', 'H: 740mm, W: 445mm, D: 330mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '93', 18, '69', '<ul><li>Fitted with premium components</li><li>Multi-function buttons</li><li>Fully backlit 3.5 inches digital LCD display screen</li><li>Easy to read pressure gauge</li><li>Uniform control opening</li><li>Cool door technology</li><li>Stylish aesthetics</li><li>Stainless steel heat exchanger</li><li>Low lift weight&nbsp;</li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623684285.jpg', 0, '<p><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Ideal boilers have made steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and Ideal is now a serious brand that’s\r\nwell worth considering. Ideal has a good reliability record, a good customer\r\nscore, and the Which? expert heating engineers rank it above average too.&nbsp;</span><br></p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Vogue GEN2 S18 System Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Vogue GEN2 S18 System Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-14 15:24:45', '2021-07-14 09:53:05'),
(235, 'Ideal Vogue GEN2 S26 System Gas Boiler', 'ideal-vogue-gen2-s26-system-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">The Ideal Vogue Gen2 S26 is a reliable gas system boiler with an\r\noutput rating of 26kW, which is best suited for medium-sized homes with up to 15\r\nradiators and 1-2 bathrooms.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">If your home has more than 15 radiators and requires more power\r\nthan the Ideal Vogue Gen2 26kW, then the 32kW may be better suited to your home. Ideal has also created the Ideal Vogue Gen2 system boiler in 15kW and 18kW for homes with lesser demand.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">With a system boiler, you are guaranteed hot water on demand. This is because once the cold water from the boiler unit reaches optimum temperature, it is then stored in a hot water cylinder until needed. The most important elements of the hot\r\nwater and heating system, such as the pump and expansion vessel, are pre-built into\r\nthe boiler itself, meaning that installation and any future maintenance and\r\nservicing should be quick and easy.</p>', 2, 3, 95, NULL, 'https://idealheating.com/uploads/documents/216174-5-vogue-system-gen2-user-guide.pdf', '1', '26', 'H: 740mm, W: 445mm, D: 330mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '93', 26, '69', '<ul><li>Fitted with premium components</li><li>Multi-function buttons</li><li>Fully backlit 3.5 inches digital LCD display screen</li><li>Easy to read pressure gauge</li><li>Uniform control opening</li><li>Cool door technology</li><li>Stylish aesthetics</li><li>Stainless steel heat exchanger</li><li>Low lift weight&nbsp;</li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623686499.jpg', 0, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Ideal boilers have\r\nmade steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and\r\nIdeal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good\r\nreliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers\r\nrank it above average too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Vogue GEN2 S26 System Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Vogue GEN2 S26 System Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-14 16:01:39', '2021-07-14 14:05:17'),
(236, 'Ideal Vogue GEN2 S32 System Gas Boiler', 'ideal-vogue-gen2-s32-system-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">The Ideal Vogue Gen S32 is a reliable system boiler\r\nwith an efficiency rating of 93% and an ErP A-rating for both central heating\r\nand hot water, meaning that this system boiler could help you to lower your\r\nenergy bills.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">With an output rating of 32kW, the Ideal Vogue Gen2 S32\r\nis the most powerful in its range, powerful enough to heat a medium to\r\nlarge-sized home with up to 20 radiators and up to 2 bathrooms. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">However, many\r\nsmaller homes do not require this demand for central heating and hot water. In\r\nthis case, if your home has lesser demand then the Ideal Vogue Gen2 S15, S18 or\r\nS26 could be more suited to you and your home. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The\r\nimportant elements for the hot water and heating system, such as the pump and\r\nexpansion vessel, are already pre-built into a system boiler, making it quicker and\r\neasier to install. However, i</span>t is important to\r\nnote that when purchasing a new or replacement system boiler, you will also\r\nneed a hot water cylinder, which is typically installed in an airing cupboard. For this reason, we do not recommend system boilers to homes with limited space.&nbsp;</p>', 2, 3, 95, NULL, 'https://idealheating.com/uploads/documents/216174-5-vogue-system-gen2-user-guide.pdf', '1', '32', 'H: 740mm, W: 445mm, D: 330mm', 'N/A', 'A', '10', '93', 32, '69', '<ul><li>Fitted with premium components</li><li>Multi-function buttons</li><li>Fully backlit 3.5 inches digital LCD display screen</li><li>Easy to read pressure gauge</li><li>Uniform control opening</li><li>Cool door technology</li><li>Stylish aesthetics</li><li>Stainless steel heat exchanger</li><li>Low lift weight&nbsp;</li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623687421.jpg', 0, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Ideal boilers have\r\nmade steady improvements in the Which? annual survey over the past few years, and\r\nIdeal is now a serious brand that’s well worth considering. Ideal has a good\r\nreliability record, a good customer score, and the Which? expert heating engineers\r\nrank it above average too.&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, 'Ideal Vogue GEN2 S32 System Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Ideal Vogue GEN2 S32 System Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-14 16:17:01', '2021-07-14 09:50:07'),
(241, 'Potterton Assure 25kW Combi Gas Boiler', 'potterton-assure-25kw-combi-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Potterton Assure 25kW combi boiler is a highly dependable\r\ngas boiler that has been designed to be neatly wall-mounted in replacement of a standard\r\nkitchen cupboard, out of sight, out of mind. This is thanks to its low lift\r\nweight of 29kg and its compact design. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">With a high-efficiency rating of 93% and an ErP A-rating for\r\nheating and hot water, this combi boiler could potentially help you to reduce\r\nboth your carbon footprint and your energy bills. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Combi\r\nboilers are ideal for smaller homes with limited space, this is because they\r\nremove the need for any additional hot or cold water storage tanks as you would\r\nneed for a regular or system boiler. They are also great for those who have a\r\ndemand for instant hot water, this is because a combi boiler is supplied with\r\ncold water directly from the mains, which is then heated and distributed to\r\nyour taps and radiators when needed. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-im