(287, 'Potterton Gold 24kW System Gas Boiler', 'potterton-gold-24kw-system-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Potterton Gold 24kW system is a highly reliable gas\r\nboiler with an efficiency rating of 89% and an ErP A-rating for central\r\nheating. Thanks to its ratings, this system boiler could potentially help you\r\nto reduce not only your carbon footprint but also help to reduce your energy\r\nbills. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Potterton gold system range has 3 different boilers with\r\ndifferent output ratings between 18kw and 28kW. This particular system boiler\r\nsits at the middle of the range, with an output of 24kW. This system boiler is\r\nideal for medium-sized homes with up to 15 radiators and a bathroom. However, if more power is what your home requires, the 28kW\r\nis available. If your home has lesser demand for central heating and\r\nhot water, then the 18kW may be better suited to your home.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">A system boiler is ideal for those who have a demand for\r\ninstant hot water. However, it is important to remember when buying a new or\r\nreplacement system boiler, that you will need to accommodate for an additional\r\nhot water storage tank. Although the unit itself is compact and lightweight, if\r\nyou have a smaller home with limited space, a system boiler may not be the best\r\noption for you. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">However, if the Potterton Gold is the boiler you desire, it\r\nis also available as a combi boiler for those with limited space in their\r\nhomes.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', 2, 8, 108, NULL, 'https://baxi-public.partsarena.com/Documents/Document?manufacturerId=235&productType=Boiler&productRange=Gold%20ErP&modelId=11249&documentId=3875&documentName=Potterton%20Gold%20System%20ErP%2018%2C24%2C28%20Installation%20(7647623-02)%20Serial%20no%20Ending%20BC', '1', '24', 'H: 780mm, W: 450mm, D: 345mm', 'N/A', 'A', '2', '89', 24, '70', '<ul><li>Pre-plumbing jig for faster installation&nbsp;</li><li>Compact design&nbsp;</li><li>Low-life weight&nbsp;</li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Easy to use controls</li><li>Flue options for flexibility during installation</li><li>Easy to read display screen&nbsp; &nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1623846299.jpg', 0, '<p><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Potterton is a good boiler brand that has a good\r\nreliability record and a good customer score. Engineers rate it well across the\r\nboard too. Overall Potterton gets a Which? brand score of 70%, which puts it in\r\na high quality tier of brands that sit just below our Best Buy cut off.&nbsp;</span><br></p>', NULL, NULL, 'Potterton Gold 24kW System Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Potterton Gold 24kW System Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-16 12:24:59', '2021-07-15 11:13:38'),
(288, 'Potterton Gold 28kW System Gas Boiler', 'potterton-gold-28kw-system-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Potterton Gold 28kW is the most powerful boiler in its\r\nrange, with an output of 28kW, ideal for larger homes with a higher demand for\r\ncentral heating and hot water. Thanks to its efficiency rating of 89% and an\r\nErP A rating, this boiler can also help you to potentially reduce your energy\r\nbills. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">With the highest output of its range, this system boiler can\r\ncomfortably heat a home with up to 20 radiators and a bathroom. However,\r\nsmaller homes may not require this high a kW output for central heating and hot water, in\r\nthis case, the Potterton Gold 18kW or 24kW may be better suited to your home. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">It is important to note when purchasing a new or replacement\r\nsystem boiler that you will need to accommodate for an additional hot water storage\r\ntank. This is because system boilers are fed with cold water directly from the\r\nmains, this water is then heated in the unit and then transferred to a sealed\r\nhot water storage tank once reaching optimum temperature. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">System boilers are ideal for those who have a high demand\r\nfor hot water, however, if space is limited in your home, you may be better off choosing a combi boiler as you will need space for a storage tank with a system boiler.\r\nLuckily, the Potterton Gold is also available as a combi boiler for those with\r\nlimited space in their homes.</p>', 2, 8, 108, NULL, 'https://baxi-public.partsarena.com/Documents/Document?manufacturerId=235&productType=Boiler&productRange=Gold%20ErP&modelId=11249&documentId=3875&documentName=Potterton%20Gold%20System%20ErP%2018%2C24%2C28%20Installation%20(7647623-02)%20Serial%20no%20Ending%20BC', '1', '28', 'H