(372, 'Vokera Mynute 35HE System Gas Boiler', 'vokera-mynute-35he-system-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Vokera Mynute 35HE system gas boiler has an output of\r\n35kW, ideal for larger homes with up to 20 radiators and 1-2 bathrooms. A high-efficiency rating of 88.8% and an ErP B-rating also means that this\r\nmodel is not only highly reliable, but can help reduce your carbon footprint and\r\nenergy bills, depending on your current boilers efficiency rating.&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">It is important to note when considering purchasing a new or\r\nreplacement system boiler, that you will need to accommodate space for an\r\nadditional hot water storage cylinder and therefore are not recommended for\r\nhomes with limited space. However, don’t let this put you off because system\r\nboilers are perfect for those with a high demand for instant hot water. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Despite needing an additional hot water tank, the system boiler unit itself has been designed to be lightweight and compact, which is one of the great benefits\r\nof this boiler. These features mean that installation can be quick and easy and can also be installed inside a standard kitchen cupboard, out\r\nof sight, out of mind.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', 2, 10, 135, NULL, 'https://www.vokera.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/mynute-he-installation-and-servicing-manual.pdf', '1', '35', 'H: 780mm, W: 450mm, D: 358mm', 'N/A', 'A', '5', '88', 35, '46', '<ul><li>Simple to operate with easy to use controls</li><li>Built-in frost protection&nbsp;</li><li>LED digital display screen</li><li>An easy to read pressure gauge&nbsp;</li><li>Easy set-up&nbsp;</li></ul>', 'finish_1624021719.jpg', 0, '<p><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Vokera boilers have a good reliability record, but its\r\ncustomers aren’t particularly fond of their boilers, and heating engineers rate\r\nother brands higher too. The overall Which? score for Vokera boilers is 476,\r\nwhich is below average.&nbsp;</span><br></p>', NULL, NULL, 'Vokera Mynute 35HE System Gas Boiler', 'Everything you need to know about the Vokera Mynute 35HE System Gas Boiler. Including an overview of the boiler, key statistics including dimensions and flow rate, and the boilers review score.', '2021-06-18 13:08:39', '2021-07-19 10:59:16'),
(373, 'Vokera Mynute i20 System Gas Boiler', 'vokera-mynute-i20-system-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The\r\nVokera Mynute i is a newer range of system boiler with outputs of 20kW and\r\n30kW. Thanks to\r\nits efficiency rating of 89.5% and ErP B-rating for heat, the Mynute i20 system\r\nboiler can help reduce your carbon footprint\r\nand energy bills if your boiler is older, but there are more efficient boilers available to increase your savings further.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The\r\nVokera i20 is a compact and lightweight system boiler, that can be installed\r\ninto a standard kitchen cupboard, so you don’t have to worry about it ruining\r\nyour aesthetics. However, it is\r\nimportant to note when considering purchasing a new or replacement system\r\nboiler, is that you will need to accommodate space for an additional storage\r\ncylinder for your hot water. For this reason, system boilers are not\r\nrecommended for homes with limited space. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">With an kW output of 20kW, the i20 is the least powerful of its range, however, it’s\r\npowerful enough to heat a home with up to 15 radiators and a single bathroom.\r\nIf you are looking for a boiler that can meet higher demands for\r\ncentral heating and hot water