(465, 'Alpha ProTec Plus 70 System Gas Boiler', 'alpha-protec-plus-70-system-gas-boiler', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">The Alpha ProTec Plus 70 is a highly efficient and reliable system gas boiler, thanks to its rating of 92% for efficiency and ErP A-rating for central heating and hot water.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">Designed to be perfectly suited for larger properties with excessive demand for both hot water and central heating, the ProTec Plus 70 has an output reach of 74kW. This boiler model is powerful enough to heat a home or property with up to 20 radiators and two bathrooms with bathtubs and showers. This system boiler would also be ideal for larger properties and office space etc.&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">Although system boilers are great for properties that require instant hot water, it is important to note that when purchasing a new or replacement system boiler, you will need to accommodate room for an additional hot water storage tank. With a system boiler, water is supplied directly from the mains, heated up, and then stored inside a hot water storage tank. For this reason, we do not recommend system boilers for properties with limited space.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:\r\n12.0pt;margin-left:0cm\">Most of the important parts of the hot water and heating system, such as the pump and expansion vessel 