(43, 'comparison_firstcontainer_boilertype', '<h2>Searching by Boiler Type</h2><p>Most homes in the U.K have one of three different types of boiler. We’ve written an article on <a href=\"https://www.warmzilla.co.uk/blog/boiler-types-explained\" target=\"_blank\"><font color=\"#ff9c00\">how to identify what boiler type</font></a> you have, but here is a quick breakdown:</p><p><br></p><p><b>Combi Boiler</b> - connected to mains water. No tanks or cylinders.<br><b>System Boiler</b> - hot water cylinder but no cold water tank in attic.<br><b>Regular Boiler</b> - hot water cylinder and cold water tank in attic.</p><p><br></p><p>When you get a new boiler fitted you can change over to a combi boiler if you want to save some space.</p>', NULL, '2021-06-29 14:07:26'),
